SUMMARY:[Maine Attorney General] Statement of Attorney General Aaron M. Fr
 ey on the Supreme Court’s ruling on West Virginia v. B.P.J.
DESCRIPTION:Statement of Attorney General Aaron M. Frey on the Supreme Cou
 rt’s ruling on West Virginia v. B.P.J. \n          <p><time datetime="20
 26-06-30T12:00:00Z">6/30/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n<span><span>Jules.M.Olso
 n@…</span></span>\n\n<span><time datetime="2026-06-30T11:46:17-04:00" ti
 tle="Tuesday\, June 30\, 2026 - 11:46">Tue\, 06/30/2026 - 11:46</time>\n</
 span>\n\n  <div>\n                  <div>\n          <p><strong>FOR IMMEDI
 ATE RELEASE</strong></p><p>Contact: Danna Hayes\, <a href="mailto:Danna.ha
 yes@maine.gov">Danna.hayes@maine.gov</a></p><p><strong>Statement of Attorn
 ey General Aaron M. Frey on the Supreme Court’s ruling on </strong><em><
 strong>West Virginia v. B.P.J.</strong></em></p><p><strong>“</strong>Tod
 ay’s ruling\, while predictable\, is yet another disturbing affront to p
 ersonal liberties by providing states with a license to discriminate. The 
 Court was clear that this decision had no bearing with respect to a state
 ’s choice to include transgender athletes and as such\, will not implica
 te the Department of Justice’s case against Maine. We will continue to d
 efend Maine’s law.”</p>\n        </div>\n            </div>\nhttps://w
 ww.maine.gov/ag/news-and-library/press-releases/statement-attorney-general
 -aaron-m-frey-supreme-courts-ruling-west
URL:https://www.maine.gov/ag/news-and-library/press-releases/statement-att
 orney-general-aaron-m-frey-supreme-courts-ruling-west
