SUMMARY:[Maine Attorney General] Statement of the Office of the Maine Atto
 rney General on Abuse of Data Breach Reporting System
DESCRIPTION:Statement of the Office of the Maine Attorney General on Abuse
  of Data Breach Reporting System\n          <p><time datetime="2026-06-12T
 12:00:00Z">6/12/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n<span><span>Jules.M.Olson@…</sp
 an></span>\n\n<span><time datetime="2026-06-12T11:06:32-04:00" title="Frid
 ay\, June 12\, 2026 - 11:06">Fri\, 06/12/2026 - 11:06</time>\n</span>\n\n 
  <div>\n                  <div>\n          <div><p lang="EN-US" xml:lang="
 EN-US"><strong>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</strong></p></div><div><p lang="EN-US
 " xml:lang="EN-US">Contact: Danna Hayes\, <a href="mailto:Danna.hayes@main
 e.gov" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Danna.Hayes@maine.gov</a>
 </p></div><div><p lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"><strong>Statement of the O
 ffice of the Maine Attorney General on Abuse of Data Breach Reporting Syst
 em</strong></p></div><div><p lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US">The Office of t
 he Maine Attorney General has been made aware of an apparent abuse of our 
 data breach reporting system. After conversations with VRChat\, one of two
  affected companies\, it has become clear that the reported data breaches 
 were hoaxes submitted by an unknown entity unrelated to either company. Th
 ese false reports have been removed from the database. We have no knowledg
 e of any recent legitimate data breach reports from either VRChat or Disco
 rd.</p></div><div><p lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US">We are reviewing our pr
 ocedures to make this abuse less likely in the future while preserving the
  public availability of such information. The public-facing database will 
 remain offline until then. In the interim\, if you are an entity who needs
  to submit a data breach report\, you can continue to do so through <a hre
 f="https://me.accessgov.com/ag/Forms/Page/ag/reportingform" rel="noreferre
 r noopener" target="_blank">our online reporting service</a>. If you need 
 information from existing reports\, please contact us at <a href="mailto:A
 G.ConsumerProtectionDivision@maine.gov" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="
 _blank">AG.ConsumerProtectionDivisio\nhttps://www.maine.gov/ag/news-and-li
 brary/press-releases/statement-office-maine-attorney-general-abuse-data-br
 each-reporting
URL:https://www.maine.gov/ag/news-and-library/press-releases/statement-off
 ice-maine-attorney-general-abuse-data-breach-reporting
CATEGORIES:Maine Attorney General
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
